---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { SITE } from "../../config/site";
const url = `${SITE.URL}/privacy/`;
---
<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy - Sezarr" description="Comprehensive privacy policy for Sezarr insurance guide website including data collection, usage, and user rights" {url}>
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-[var(--max-w)] px-4 py-10">
    <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300"><strong>Effective Date:</strong> September 25, 2025</p>
      
      <p>Sezarr ("we," "us," or "our") respects your privacy and is committed to protecting your personal information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you visit our website sezarr.com.</p>

      <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
      
      <h3>Information You Provide</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Contact Forms:</strong> Name, email address, phone number, and messages you send through contact forms</li>
        <li><strong>Calculator Inputs:</strong> Information entered into insurance calculators (age, location, coverage preferences, etc.)</li>
        <li><strong>Newsletter Subscriptions:</strong> Email addresses for newsletter subscriptions</li>
        <li><strong>Feedback and Comments:</strong> Any feedback, reviews, or comments you provide</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Information Automatically Collected</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Website Analytics:</strong> IP address, browser type, device information, pages visited, time spent, referring websites</li>
        <li><strong>Cookies and Tracking:</strong> Session cookies, preference cookies, analytics cookies</li>
        <li><strong>Location Data:</strong> General location information based on IP address</li>
        <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Calculator usage, page interactions, search queries on our site</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
      
      <h3>Primary Uses</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Service Provision:</strong> To provide insurance calculators, guides, and educational content</li>
        <li><strong>Communication:</strong> To respond to your inquiries and provide customer support</li>
        <li><strong>Website Improvement:</strong> To analyze usage patterns and improve our content and functionality</li>
        <li><strong>Legal Compliance:</strong> To comply with applicable laws and regulations</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Marketing and Analytics</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Content Personalization:</strong> To provide relevant insurance information based on your interests</li>
        <li><strong>Email Communications:</strong> To send newsletters and updates (with your consent)</li>
        <li><strong>Performance Analytics:</strong> To understand how our website and calculators are used</li>
        <li><strong>Affiliate Programs:</strong> To track referrals and commissions (anonymized where possible)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Information Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
      
      <h3>Third-Party Service Providers</h3>
      <p>We may share your information with trusted third parties who assist us in operating our website:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Analytics Providers:</strong> Google Analytics, other website analytics services</li>
        <li><strong>Email Services:</strong> Email newsletter and communication platforms</li>
        <li><strong>Hosting Providers:</strong> Website hosting and content delivery networks</li>
        <li><strong>Customer Support:</strong> Help desk and customer support platforms</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Insurance Partners and Affiliates</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Quote Requests:</strong> If you request insurance quotes, we may share your information with licensed insurance providers</li>
        <li><strong>Affiliate Networks:</strong> Anonymous usage data may be shared with affiliate partners for commission tracking</li>
        <li><strong>Lead Generation:</strong> With your explicit consent, we may share your contact information with insurance professionals</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Legal Requirements</h3>
      <p>We may disclose your information if required by law, court order, or government regulation, or to protect our legal rights and safety.</p>

      <h2>Data Security</h2>
      
      <p>We implement appropriate technical and organizational security measures to protect your personal information:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Encryption:</strong> SSL/TLS encryption for data transmission</li>
        <li><strong>Access Controls:</strong> Limited access to personal information on a need-to-know basis</li>
        <li><strong>Regular Updates:</strong> Security patches and software updates</li>
        <li><strong>Data Minimization:</strong> We collect only the information necessary for our services</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
      
      <h3>Types of Cookies We Use</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Essential Cookies:</strong> Required for website functionality (cannot be disabled)</li>
        <li><strong>Analytics Cookies:</strong> Help us understand website usage and performance</li>
        <li><strong>Preference Cookies:</strong> Remember your settings and preferences</li>
        <li><strong>Marketing Cookies:</strong> Track interactions for affiliate and advertising purposes</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Cookie Management</h3>
      <p>You can manage cookie preferences through:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Our cookie consent banner (appears on first visit)</li>
        <li>Your browser settings (disable/enable cookies)</li>
        <li>Third-party opt-out tools (Google Analytics opt-out, etc.)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Your Rights and Choices</h2>
      
      <h3>General Rights</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Access:</strong> Request information about what personal data we collect and how it's used</li>
        <li><strong>Correction:</strong> Request correction of inaccurate or incomplete information</li>
        <li><strong>Deletion:</strong> Request deletion of your personal information (subject to legal requirements)</li>
        <li><strong>Opt-Out:</strong> Unsubscribe from marketing communications at any time</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>State-Specific Rights</h3>
      
      <h4>California Residents (CCPA/CPRA)</h4>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Right to Know:</strong> Request disclosure of personal information collected, used, and shared</li>
        <li><strong>Right to Delete:</strong> Request deletion of personal information</li>
        <li><strong>Right to Opt-Out:</strong> Opt-out of the "sale" of personal information</li>
        <li><strong>Right to Non-Discrimination:</strong> Equal service regardless of privacy rights exercised</li>
      </ul>
      
      <p><strong>California "Do Not Sell" Request:</strong> <a href="/privacy/do-not-sell/" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-700">Click here to opt-out of information sharing</a></p>

      <h4>Other State Privacy Laws</h4>
      <p>We comply with applicable state privacy laws including Virginia (VCDPA), Colorado (CPA), and Connecticut (CTDPA). Contact us to exercise your rights under these laws.</p>

      <h2>Data Retention</h2>
      
      <p>We retain personal information for as long as necessary to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Provide our services and respond to your requests</li>
        <li>Comply with legal obligations and resolve disputes</li>
        <li>Maintain accurate business records</li>
        <li>Improve our services and website functionality</li>
      </ul>
      
      <p><strong>Typical Retention Periods:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Contact Form Data:</strong> 3 years from last contact</li>
        <li><strong>Analytics Data:</strong> 26 months (Google Analytics default)</li>
        <li><strong>Email Subscriptions:</strong> Until you unsubscribe plus 1 year</li>
        <li><strong>Calculator Usage:</strong> Anonymized after 30 days</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
      
      <p>Our website is not directed to children under 13 years of age. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you believe we have collected information from a child under 13, please contact us immediately.</p>

      <h2>International Data Transfers</h2>
      
      <p>Your information may be transferred to and processed in countries other than your country of residence. We ensure appropriate safeguards are in place for international transfers in compliance with applicable privacy laws.</p>

      <h2>Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
      
      <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or applicable laws. We will notify you of material changes by:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Posting the updated policy on our website</li>
        <li>Updating the "Effective Date" at the top of this policy</li>
        <li>Sending email notifications for significant changes (if you've subscribed)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Contact Information</h2>
      
      <p>If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or wish to exercise your privacy rights, please contact us:</p>
      
      <div class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800 p-4 rounded-lg">
        <p><strong>Email:</strong> privacy@sezarr.com</p>
        <p><strong>Mail:</strong> Privacy Officer, Sezarr<br>
        [Address to be added]</p>
        <p><strong>Response Time:</strong> We will respond to privacy requests within 30 days</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 dark:bg-blue-900/20 border-l-4 border-blue-400 p-4 mt-8">
        <p class="font-semibold text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-200 mb-2">ðŸ”’ Your Privacy Matters</p>
        <p class="text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-300">We are committed to protecting your privacy and using your information responsibly. If you have any concerns about how your information is handled, please don't hesitate to contact us.</p>
      </div>

      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mt-8 pt-4 border-t">
        <strong>Last Updated:</strong> September 25, 2025<br>
        <strong>Next Review Date:</strong> March 25, 2026
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
